{"article_id":"HRDxdldwIoBF4BYz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Trump looks like he might be gearing up to touch the third rail of immigration policy in 2017 :","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"ending the Obama-era Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"which allowed young unauthorized immigrants to work legally","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"and protected them from deportation .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Axios reported Thursday night","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"that Trump is \" seriously considering \" ending DACA ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"after months of refusing to make a decision about the future of the 780,000 immigrants","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"it ' s protected .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"He ' ll have to make a decision in the next few weeks .","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"A group of state officials ,","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"led by Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton ,","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"is threatening to sue the administration","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"to end DACA","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"if Trump doesn ' t pull the plug by September 5","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"- which could result in the program being put on hold in federal courts .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"But politically and legislatively , ending DACA could open the floodgates .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"The unauthorized immigrants","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"it protects","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"are politically sympathetic and well-connected","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"they ' ve gone to school in the US ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"are fluent in English ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"and may not have even known","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"they weren ' t in the country legally","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"before applying to college .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"Some polling finds","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Americans oppose ending the program by a two-to-one margin .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"That may be why Trump has been reticent to kill DACA ,","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"even as he ' s cracked down on immigration enforcement in his first months in office .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"In July , he told reporters","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"he ' s still wrestling with it :","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"`` It ' s a decision","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"that I make","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"and it ' s a decision","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"that ' s very , very hard to make . \"","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Trump ' s own White House is divided -","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Attorney General Jeff Sessions","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"( who would be in charge","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"of defending DACA in court","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"if the state officials ' lawsuit went forward )","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"wants to kill it ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"while the Department of Homeland Security","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"( which was , until recently , led by Trump Chief of Staff John Kelly )","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"is reticent to get rid of the only remaining vestige of President Obama ' s efforts","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"to prioritize deportations","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"so that long-resident unauthorized immigrants with no criminal records weren ' t targeted .","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"But the threat of a lawsuit may have tipped the scales .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"And then all legislative hell could break loose .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"The Trump administration has had several opportunities","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"to end DACA -","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"either by nullifying the existing protections for the 780,000 people","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"who ' ve already been approved under the program","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"or by refusing to accept any new people","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"or renew the two-year protections for existing DACA recipients","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"when they expire .","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"It hadn ' t taken any of them yet .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Even when it formally killed an abortive 2014 program","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"expanding deferred action ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"it explicitly made clear","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"that it wasn ' t killing the program","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"that was already in effect .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"This has been a sore spot for immigration hardliners ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"who understood Trump ' s campaign promise","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"to roll back President Obama ' s \" unconstitutional executive orders \" as a promise","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"to end DACA .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"( DACA ' s constitutionality hasn ' t been successfully challenged ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"but immigration hawks believe","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"the president ' s legal authority","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"to protect immigrants from deportation in individual cases","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"doesn ' t extend to a program","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"that allowed certain immigrants to apply en masse . )","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"In June , a group of 10 Republican state officials ,","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"led by Texas AG Paxton ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"took matters into their own hands .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"They wrote the administration a letter","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"asking them to end the DACA program -","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"and threatening to file a federal lawsuit over the program ' s constitutionality","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"if the administration failed to act .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"That letter changed the calculus","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"about whether to end DACA","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"in two big ways .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"First of all , it shifted the focus from the Department of Homeland Security ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"which administers the program","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"- and whose secretary , John Kelly , appears loath to go after DACA recipients -","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"and toward the Department of Justice ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"which would have to defend DACA","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"if the states took it to court .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"That means , ultimately , it would come down to US Attorney General Jeff Sessions","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"- a longtime immigration hardliner on legal and unauthorized immigration -","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"as to whether , and how , to stand up for the program .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"While Sessions ' s relationship with Trump has been strained for much of his presidency ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"it ' s clear he has a lot of influence on this issue .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"In July , then-Homeland Security Secretary Kelly told members of the Congressional Hispanic Caucus","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"that the decision about DACA was entirely up to Sessions .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"even if Trump decided to overrule his AG ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"it ' s not clear how he could compel him to forcefully defend a program in court","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"that Sessions wants to end .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"It might not matter anyway .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"Here ' s the other way","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"the state AGs ' letter changed the calculus :","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"If the administration doesn ' t end DACA ,","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"and the states sue them over it ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"the program will likely be put on hold","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"- at least temporarily -","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"by a federal judge .","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"The challenge to DACA would be used","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"to revive the suit against the 2014 deferred action program","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"- which guarantees","depth":16},{"id":109,"text":"it would be heard by Southern District of Texas Judge Andrew Hanen .","depth":16},{"id":110,"text":"Republican state officials selected Hanen ' s court","depth":16},{"id":111,"text":"when they challenged the 2014 deferred action program ,","depth":16},{"id":112,"text":"and he hasn ' t disappointed them -","depth":15},{"id":113,"text":"he ' s clearly skeptical of the government ' s actions","depth":16},{"id":114,"text":"to limit immigration enforcement .","depth":16},{"id":115,"text":"It ' s not an ironclad guarantee","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"that Hanen would rule against DACA ,","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"but it ' s a pretty safe bet .","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"And the fairly conservative Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals might agree .","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"Under those circumstances , the program would at least be on hold for months or even years .","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"And not only would the administration ' s hand have been forced ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"but it would look like a loss for Trump","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"yet another court defeat on immigration , this time from the other side .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"It ' s not hard to imagine that President Trump might want to avoid a public loss .","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"If he ' s convinced","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"that DACA is going to end anyway ,","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"he may choose to do it himself -","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"no matter how sympathetic he feels toward the DREAMers .","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"If DACA falls ,","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"it could start a chain reaction in Congress","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"The deadline","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"given by the state attorneys general in their letter to the administration","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"was September 5 .","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"That happens to be the day","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"Congress is slated to return from its August recess .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"Congress can ' t stop the Trump administration from ending DACA ,","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"or Republican state governments from suing","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"if it doesn ' t .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"if DACA does end ,","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"the pressure","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"to act","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"shifts to the legislative branch .","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"While immigration isn ' t nearly as bipartisan an issue","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"as it used to be","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"- Democrats have overwhelmingly opposed efforts","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"to ramp up enforcement ,","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"while few Republicans are still willing to come out in favor of legalization for unauthorized immigrants -","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"there are still some Republican members of Congress","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"who want to keep DACA recipients in the US .","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"After the 2016 presidential election , members of both parties introduced a bill","depth":6},{"id":152,"text":"that would grant legal status to DACA recipients","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"in case Trump ended the program ;","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"this spring , a group of Republican members of the House introduced their own legalization bill ,","depth":6},{"id":155,"text":"called the \" Recognizing America ' s Children \"","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"( RAC )","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"Act .","depth":7},{"id":158,"text":"Those bills haven ' t moved yet","depth":5},{"id":159,"text":"because there hasn ' t yet been a threat to DACA .","depth":5},{"id":160,"text":"But","depth":5},{"id":161,"text":"if nearly 800,000 people are suddenly forced out of their jobs and faced with the threat of deportation at any time ,","depth":6},{"id":162,"text":"supporters of legalization are likely to start pushing hard for Congress to take action .","depth":6},{"id":163,"text":"Some conservatives ,","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"whether openly or behind closed doors ,","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"admit","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"that they ' re willing to accept a compromise","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"that results in DACA recipients getting to stay in the US .","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"( After all , they ' re US-educated and fluent in English ;","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"for people","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"worried about immigrants as threats to cultural integration ,","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"DACA recipients are not the most imminent risk . )","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"But they want something in return :","depth":7},{"id":173,"text":"expanded immigration enforcement","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"to target new arrivals and unauthorized immigrants","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"living in the US ,","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"cuts to legal immigration in the future , or both .","depth":8},{"id":177,"text":"The White House itself is reportedly envisioning a grand bargain :","depth":7},{"id":178,"text":"In return for allowing DACA recipients to become legal immigrants ,","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"they want future cuts to legal immigration","depth":10},{"id":180,"text":"( possibly in the form of the Trump-endorsed RAISE Act ,","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"which would cut legal immigration to the US in half over the next decade ) ;","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"mandatory verification of legal status for anyone","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"hired for a job in the US ;","depth":11},{"id":184,"text":"and expanded funding for border","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"( including a wall )","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"and interior enforcement .","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"Right now , Democrats aren ' t willing to agree to any of this .","depth":7},{"id":188,"text":"They ' re not even interested in giving the White House a few billion dollars","depth":9},{"id":189,"text":"to build a few dozen miles of border barriers","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"- something","depth":9},{"id":191,"text":"Trump says","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"he ' s willing to shut down the government over","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"if he doesn ' t get it .","depth":10},{"id":194,"text":"The question is whether Trump will hold the line","depth":7},{"id":195,"text":"if congressional Republicans decide","depth":8},{"id":196,"text":"they ' re less interested in falling in line behind the president","depth":9},{"id":197,"text":"than they are in making a deal .","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"And","depth":7},{"id":199,"text":"if they are ,","depth":8},{"id":200,"text":"the question is what kind of deal they would accept .","depth":8},{"id":201,"text":"Several factions in Congress have been pushing narrower bills","depth":8},{"id":202,"text":"to deal with discrete aspects of immigration policy","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"-","depth":7},{"id":204,"text":"but the White House ' s desire","depth":8},{"id":205,"text":"to think bigger","depth":8},{"id":206,"text":"might be inspiring those factions to ask for more too .","depth":7},{"id":207,"text":"The possibilities aren ' t endless ,","depth":6},{"id":208,"text":"but they ' re close .","depth":6},{"id":209,"text":"Once Congress agrees to crack open the door on immigration ,","depth":6},{"id":210,"text":"it ' s going to be hard to keep it from opening all the way , into a free-for-all over immigration policy writ large .","depth":6},{"id":211,"text":"And","depth":7},{"id":212,"text":"if DACA ends ,","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"there ' s going to be a lot of pressure on Congress","depth":9},{"id":214,"text":"to open that door for the sake of nearly 800,000 American-raised DREAMers .","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"House Speaker Paul Ryan","depth":9},{"id":216,"text":"( and , to a lesser extent , Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell )","depth":9},{"id":217,"text":"really doesn ' t want this fight .","depth":8},{"id":218,"text":"It would expose the fissures in his party between traditional pro-business conservatives","depth":10},{"id":219,"text":"who have been open to some form of legalization","depth":11},{"id":220,"text":"- like Ryan himself -","depth":11},{"id":221,"text":"and the hardline populists","depth":10},{"id":222,"text":"who rose to power over the past few years","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"and are currently sitting in the White House .","depth":11},{"id":224,"text":"It would bog down the congressional agenda at a time","depth":9},{"id":225,"text":"when Congress is already worried about getting everything done .","depth":9},{"id":226,"text":"And it certainly looks like Trump himself doesn ' t want this fight .","depth":6},{"id":227,"text":"He told reporters Thursday","depth":9},{"id":228,"text":"that he wants a \" comprehensive \" solution on immigration","depth":11},{"id":229,"text":"( though it ' s not clear what \" comprehensive \" means to Donald Trump )","depth":11},{"id":230,"text":"but that the politics \" aren ' t ready . \"","depth":10},{"id":231,"text":"If they ' re not ready now ,","depth":9},{"id":232,"text":"they won ' t be ready in September .","depth":9},{"id":233,"text":"But thanks to state officials from Trump and Ryan ' s own party ,","depth":8},{"id":234,"text":"that fight might be coming ,","depth":9},{"id":235,"text":"ready or not .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":471,"left":379,"right":470,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":379,"left":244,"right":378,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":239,"right":243,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":0,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":1,"right":237,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":243,"left":242,"right":8,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":242,"left":4,"right":241,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":241,"left":5,"right":240,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":240,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":378,"left":305,"right":377,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":305,"left":261,"right":304,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":259,"right":260,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":250,"right":258,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":249,"right":15,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":249,"left":248,"right":14,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":247,"right":13,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":245,"right":246,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":245,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":252,"right":257,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":251,"right":18,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":251,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":19,"right":256,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":20,"right":255,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":255,"left":21,"right":254,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":254,"left":253,"right":24,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":260,"left":25,"right":26,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":304,"left":268,"right":303,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":268,"left":262,"right":267,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":27,"right":28,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":263,"right":266,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":263,"left":29,"right":30,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":266,"left":264,"right":265,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":264,"left":31,"right":32,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":33,"right":34,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":280,"right":302,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":280,"left":279,"right":47,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":279,"left":278,"right":46,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":278,"left":273,"right":277,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":273,"left":35,"right":272,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":272,"left":271,"right":40,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":271,"left":36,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":270,"left":37,"right":269,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":38,"right":39,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":277,"left":274,"right":276,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":41,"right":42,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":43,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":275,"left":44,"right":45,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":287,"right":301,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":287,"left":286,"right":55,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":286,"left":281,"right":285,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":48,"right":49,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":282,"right":284,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":282,"left":50,"right":51,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":284,"left":52,"right":283,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":283,"left":53,"right":54,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":291,"right":300,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":291,"left":288,"right":290,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":288,"left":56,"right":57,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":290,"left":58,"right":289,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":289,"left":59,"right":60,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":294,"right":299,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":294,"left":61,"right":293,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":293,"left":292,"right":64,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":292,"left":62,"right":63,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":65,"right":298,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":298,"left":66,"right":297,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":297,"left":295,"right":296,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":295,"left":67,"right":68,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":69,"right":70,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":377,"left":332,"right":376,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":332,"left":311,"right":331,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":311,"left":307,"right":310,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":307,"left":306,"right":73,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":306,"left":71,"right":72,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":310,"left":308,"right":309,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":308,"left":74,"right":75,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":309,"left":76,"right":77,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":331,"left":313,"right":330,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":312,"right":80,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":312,"left":78,"right":79,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":330,"l